1772819895250308	botcrit-dev	itc:v3:AWLJJzk5yTmfxAAAAAAAQdV3XdXb-AAAAAEu6QE		item.comment	bn-1mfj	{"body":"## Comprehensive Rename Scope: crit → seal\n\n### 1. Cargo.toml & Workspace Structure (4 files)\n- `ws/default/Cargo.toml`: workspace member paths `crates/crit-*` → `crates/seal-*`, workspace dependency `crit-core` → `seal-core`\n- `crates/crit-core/Cargo.toml`: package name `crit-core` → `seal-core`, description\n- `crates/crit-cli/Cargo.toml`: package name `crit-cli` → `seal-cli`, binary name `crit` → `seal`, deps `crit-core`/`crit-tui` → `seal-core`/`seal-tui`\n- `crates/crit-tui/Cargo.toml`: package name `crit-tui` → `seal-tui`, dep `crit-core` → `seal-core`\n\n### 2. Directory Renames (3 dirs + 2 dotfiles)\n- `crates/crit-core/` → `crates/seal-core/`\n- `crates/crit-cli/` → `crates/seal-cli/`\n- `crates/crit-tui/` → `crates/seal-tui/`\n- `.crit/` → `.seal/` (data directory)\n- `.critignore` → `.sealignore`\n\n### 3. Constants & Environment Variables\n- `CRIT_DIR` const (\".crit\") → `SEAL_DIR` (\".seal\") in init.rs\n- `CRIT_AGENT` env var → `SEAL_AGENT` in identity.rs\n- `CRIT_SCM` env var → `SEAL_SCM` in scm/mod.rs\n- `BOTCRIT_AGENT` env var — decision needed: keep or rename to `BOTSEAL_AGENT`?\n- `BOTCRIT_UI_THEME` env var in tui — decision needed\n\n### 4. Rust Types & Imports (~50+ files)\n- All `use crit_core::` → `use seal_core::`\n- All `use crit_cli::` → `use seal_cli::`\n- All `use crit_tui::` → `use seal_tui::`\n- Struct `CritIgnore` → `SealIgnore` (critignore.rs)\n- Variable names: `crit_root` → `seal_root`, `crit_dir` → `seal_dir`\n- File `critignore.rs` → `sealignore.rs` (module rename)\n- CLI command name: `#[command(name = \"crit\")]` → `\"seal\"` in cli/mod.rs\n\n### 5. User-Facing Strings & Help Text (~30+ locations)\n- All error messages with `crit` command examples → `seal`\n- Help text in agents.rs, init.rs, doctor.rs, helpers.rs, reviews.rs, migrate.rs\n- Example: \"Run 'crit init' first\" → \"Run 'seal init' first\"\n- Example: \"Not a crit repository\" → \"Not a seal repository\"\n- GitHub URLs: github.com/anomalyco/botcrit — decision: rename repo too?\n\n### 6. Documentation (6+ .md files)\n- README.md: title, all command examples, env var docs, .crit/ paths\n- spec.md: product name, command examples, .crit/ paths\n- AGENTS.md: project name, tool references, .crit/ paths, maw exec examples\n- docs/demo.md, docs/crit-core-crate-boundaries.md, docs/crate-split-migration.md\n- scripts/generate-demo-jj.sh, scripts/generate-demo-git.sh: var names, command examples\n\n### 7. Config & Build Files\n- Justfile: `cargo install --path crates/crit-cli` → `crates/seal-cli`\n- .critignore: self-reference `.crit/` → `.seal/`\n- .gitignore: likely no changes needed\n\n### 8. TUI-Specific\n- Temp file naming: `crit-comment-{}.md` → `seal-comment-{}.md`\n- Config dir: `.botcrit/ui.json` → decision: `.seal/ui.json` or `.botseal/ui.json`?\n- Doc comments referencing `botcrit-ui`\n\n### 9. Test Fixtures (~15+ test blocks)\n- Test paths: `/tmp/test-repo/.crit/` → `.seal/`\n- Test assertions checking for `crit --agent` → `seal --agent`\n- Files: init.rs, helpers.rs, agents.rs, doctor.rs, critignore.rs, version.rs, projection/mod.rs\n\n### 10. Open Questions (need decisions before implementation)\n1. **BOTCRIT_AGENT env var**: rename to BOTSEAL_AGENT? Or keep for backward compat?\n2. **GitHub repo**: rename anomalyco/botcrit → anomalyco/botseal?\n3. **Agent IDs**: botcrit-dev, botcrit-security — rename to seal-dev, seal-security?\n4. **Bus channel**: #botcrit → #seal?\n5. **Backward compat**: support reading old .crit/ dirs? Migration command?\n6. **.critignore filename**: .sealignore? Or keep .critignore as alias?\n\n### Estimated Scope\n~150-200 line/reference changes across ~40-50 files. The rename is mechanical but broad — a workspace with find-and-replace plus directory renames, followed by cargo test verification."}	blake3:BLctW9i7sJ-yzeyiOywMUqhz8hfiGpnfUcbAMkovGFs
1772819914467505	botcrit-dev	itc:v3:AWLJJzk5yTmfxAAAAAAAQdV3XdXb-AAAAAEu6gE		item.update	bn-1mfj	{"field":"description","value":"Rename the project from 'crit' to 'seal'. This covers:\n\n- Binary: crit → seal\n- Crate names: crit-core, crit-cli, crit-tui → seal-core, seal-cli, seal-tui\n- Directory renames: crates/crit-* → crates/seal-*, .crit/ → .seal/, .critignore → .sealignore\n- Env vars: CRIT_AGENT → SEAL_AGENT, CRIT_SCM → SEAL_SCM (BOTCRIT_AGENT TBD)\n- Rust identifiers: imports, types (CritIgnore→SealIgnore), variables (crit_root→seal_root)\n- CLI strings: all help text, error messages, command examples\n- Docs: README.md, spec.md, AGENTS.md, docs/*.md, demo scripts\n- Config: Justfile, .critignore/.sealignore\n- Tests: fixtures with .crit/ paths, assertion strings\n- TUI: temp file names, config dir path\n\nPart of a broader rebrand. ~150-200 references across ~40-50 files.\n\nOpen questions: BOTCRIT_AGENT env var rename, GitHub repo rename, agent IDs (botcrit-dev/botcrit-security), bus channel (#botcrit), backward compat for .crit/ dirs."}	blake3:nq8dPAwVYW1SKF0nD2Co5jMW339vVG9mueXqpWnIgKQ
1772820161083361	botcrit-dev	itc:v3:AWLJJzk5yTmfxAAAAAAAQdV3XdXb-AAAAAEu6wE		item.comment	bn-1mfj	{"body":"## Decisions Resolved\n\n1. **BOTCRIT_AGENT** → BOTSEAL_AGENT (yes, rename)\n2. **GitHub repo rename** — owner handles. Also fix incorrect 'anomalyco' refs → 'bobisme' everywhere\n3. **Agent IDs** — update in .edict.toml (botcrit-dev → botseal-dev, botcrit-security → botseal-security)\n4. **Bus channel** — owner handles\n5. **Backward compat** — auto-rename .crit/ → .seal/ on first run (migration)\n6. **.critignore** → .sealignore\n\nAdditional fix: GitHub URLs reference anomalyco/botcrit but should be bobisme/botcrit (and eventually bobisme/botseal)"}	blake3:r8sxaw47sHo2LDkRPziIFlAoGKDlfj8KC42wkXxDX5U
1772820175937483	botcrit-dev	itc:v3:AWLJJzk5yTmfxAAAAAAAQdV3XdXb-AAAAAEu7AE		item.comment	bn-1mfj	{"body":"## .edict.toml Changes Needed\n- Line 7: name = \"botcrit\" → \"botseal\"\n- Line 10: default_agent = \"botcrit-dev\" → \"botseal-dev\"\n- Line 11: channel = \"botcrit\" → \"botseal\" (owner handles channel, but config must match)\n- Line 18: crit = true → seal = true (tool name)\n\n## Incorrect GitHub URLs (anomalyco → bobisme)\n- crates/crit-cli/src/cli/commands/agents.rs:26 — github.com/anomalyco/botcrit\n- src/cli/commands/agents.rs:26 — same (appears to be duplicate/old location)\n- README.md:111 — git clone github.com/anomalyco/botcrit\n- src/main.rs:310 — cargo install --git github.com/anomalyco/botcrit-ui\n\nAll should be bobisme/ not anomalyco/, and will become bobisme/botseal (+ bobisme/botseal-ui)"}	blake3:oyNHmE5Z0EPIbTvZfg-jX_ST0poP4KqjSGGMqFv3pwY
1772820188352941	botcrit-dev	itc:v3:AWLJJzk5yTmfxAAAAAAAQdV3XdXb-AAAAAEu7QE		item.comment	bn-1mfj	{"body":"## Auto-Migration: .crit/ → .seal/\nNeed to add migration logic that on first run:\n1. Detects .crit/ exists but .seal/ does not\n2. Renames .crit/ → .seal/ automatically\n3. Renames .critignore → .sealignore if present\n4. Deletes index.db (projection cache) to force rebuild with new paths\n5. Prints a notice to the user about the rename\n\nBest place: early in the CLI init path (helpers.rs find_crit_root or equivalent). Could also be a dedicated 'seal migrate' subcommand, but auto-rename on first run is cleaner.\n\nSimilarly for env vars: accept both CRIT_AGENT and SEAL_AGENT during transition (check SEAL_AGENT first, fall back to CRIT_AGENT with deprecation warning). Same for CRIT_SCM/SEAL_SCM and BOTCRIT_AGENT/BOTSEAL_AGENT."}	blake3:C-qsM6VfEtty0QRPmtGuDhhEsTagfrGMzvZ_i5aup-4
